			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My first character was a Wizard, so I got to know all about the root-line <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
When root is cast, it either sticks or it is resisted off-the-bat. ("You have resisted the Root spell")
<br />

<br />
If it sticks, you have a chance to break the root when the next 'tick' expires (once every 6 seconds)
<br />

<br />
Root duration can be anything from one second to the max of the spell
<br />

<br />
You also can break root when you are hit with a DD spell (similar to the principal of mez breaking) but not always, you can possibly still be held by the root.
<br />

<br />
To my knowledge you can still use Gate when Rooted, it should not prevent you from escaping that way.
<br />

<br />
But when you want to stand your ground (no pun intended) then you want to break root.
<br />

<br />
You have two choices:
<br />

<br />
1. Stand it out and wait for it to wear off.
<br />

<br />
2. Get nuked and hope it breaks.
<br />

<br />
With 2, there is something I'm not clear on: You COULD nuke yourself to break the root, but I am not sure if it works... If it does, you could have burst of flame memmed (lvl 1 nuke) or a ceramic bracelet on you to cast on yourself in hopes of breaking the root early.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=320122" target="_blank" class="postlink">Majishia Vie </a>
<br />
59 Conjurer
<br />
Wyrd Angles
<br />
Antonius Bayle
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=827513" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fayth Vanquisher </a>
<br />
37 Paladin
<br />
Wyrd Angles
<br />
Antonius Bayle
<br />

<br />
Edina: What do you think, Pats?
<br />
Patsy: ... Well how much did it cost?
<br />
Edina: £4,000
<br />
Patsy: Oh then it's fabulous, darling!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
