				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This thread clearly started before the resist changes that launched a bit before POP.
<br />

<br />
These days it takes about 150MR to consistently resist root. That said, spells like greater immobilize and other roots that resist with a negative modifier (like our 65 earth pet's root) will require around 200+ to resist consistently and even then, it's gonna land on occasion.<br />_________________<br /><span style="color: red"><span style="font-weight: bold">Sage Svenuce Summonstuff</span></span>
